FAQ

What are the most common frozen foods?

Some of the most common frozen foods in our grocery section include the following: Vegetables, such as peas, corn, carrots, cauliflower, broccoli, and mixed vegetables Fruits, such as strawberries, mangoes, peaches, and pineapple Pizza with a variety of topping choices, such as pepperoni, hamburger, and supreme Ice cream and frozen treats, like ice cream sandwiches Fried foods, like French fries, tater tots, and hashbrowns Chicken nuggets, patties, and strips Fish fillets, fish sticks and popcorn shrimp TV dinners Frozen breakfast foods, such as waffles, pancakes, breakfast burritos, breakfast sandwichesYou���ll find a variety of frozen food to choose from at our Every Day Low Prices.

What are quick frozen foods?

Quick frozen foods are foods that have been rapidly frozen using a process called flash freezing. This involves exposing the food to very low temperatures, typically between -40 and -112 degrees Fahrenheit, for a short period of time, usually just a few minutes. This process helps to preserve the quality, texture, and flavor of the food, as well as its nutritional value.Quick frozen foods can include a wide variety of products, such as fruits, vegetables, meats, seafood, and prepared meals. Some examples include frozen berries, vegetables like peas and corn, fish fillets, chicken breasts, and frozen pizzas.Quick frozen foods are convenient and easy to store, as they can be kept in the freezer for an extended period of time without spoiling. They can be a good option for people who don't have access to fresh produce or who want to save time on meal preparation. However, it is important to read the labels and choose products that are high in nutrients and low in added sugars, salt, and unhealthy fats.

What is considered a frozen meal?

A frozen meal is a pre-packaged meal that has been frozen to extend its shelf life. These meals are typically sold in the frozen food section of grocery stores and can be cooked quickly and easily in a microwave, oven, or on a stovetop.Frozen meals can come in a variety of forms, including: Single-serve meals: These are pre-packaged meals designed for one person, often consisting of a main dish and one or two sides. Family-size meals: These are larger frozen meals designed to feed several people. Frozen pizzas: These are pre-made pizzas that can be cooked in the oven or on a stovetop. Frozen breakfasts: These are pre-packaged breakfast meals, such as pancakes, waffles, and breakfast sandwiches. Frozen desserts: These are pre-made desserts that can be thawed and served, such as ice cream, cakes, and pies.Frozen meals can be a convenient option for busy people who don't have time to cook from scratch. However, it's important to read the labels and choose frozen meals that are high in nutrients and low in added sugars, salt, and unhealthy fats.

About Frozen Foods - Walmart.com

Stock your freezer with delicious frozen meals and snacks

Fresh foods like meat, fish, vegetables and fruit are great ingredient choices when you're prepping meals for your family. Sometimes though, time constraints from work, school and life in general might mean you don't have the time to make a wholesome meal or quick snack from scratch. Or, maybe you're planning on feeding a big group and still want to serve something delicious that doesn't require much prepping. Turn to versatile frozen meals to satisfy everyone. With a wide selection of frozen foods stocking your freezer, you can make complete meals in a matter of minutes and still know you're keeping your family happy and healthy. Check out what we have to offer. All of it's available at our Every Day Low Prices, making it easy to stock up on tasty lunches, dinners, snacks and desserts.

Frozen dinners and meals

Back during the middle of the of the 20th century, a frozen dinner then commonly known as a TV dinner routinely featured a meat dish, a vegetable, a starch and a dessert. The selections were limited and hardly memorable. Fast forward to the 21st century, and frozen dinners are virtually as good as their homemade counterparts. You can even get restaurant-quality dinners that your favorite restaurant chains have created. The variety available is as vast as your imagination and covers many different cultures, including Italian, Mexican and Chinese favorites.

Meal selections available include many different pasta dishes, from standard fare like lasagna and macaroni and cheese to more modern takes like blackened chicken Alfredo and pesto tortellini. If you're looking to make a quick hot sandwich, select a frozen option like chicken with barbecue sauce or a Philly cheesesteak. There are even breakfast sandwiches with morning favorites like eggs and Canadian bacon on English muffins or sausage, egg and cheese biscuits. Virtually anything you can make from scratch, you can find in our frozen food section even old-school favorites like TV dinners and pot pies.

Then, there's pizza. Frozen pizza is a favorite for kids and adults alike, and it's a must have for busy weeknights or after-school snacks. You can find inexpensive frozen pizzas that have classic toppings on them and gourmet pizzas that have the kind of ingredients you find only in a pizza parlor some of them even rival what you might have delivered to your home. There are also pizza-type snacks available, including pastry pockets, pizza rolls and pizza bagels.

Frozen meat and seafood

You typically have to fire up the grill in your backyard to cook a juicy burger or, at the very least, head to your favorite fast-food restaurant to pick one up. Instead of all that work, you can simply heat one up in your microwave, add some of your favorite condiments to a bun and have a grilled burger ready to eat in the same amount of time it takes to get the charcoal going. But, the meat options don t end there. If you have kids, you know how much they like chicken nuggets and chicken strips. Instead of going through the drive-through window, make their favorite snack at home in your oven. If ribeye steak or chicken wings and shrimp are your thing, make surf-and-turf with fresh ingredients right from your freezer.

Other kid-friendly snack ideas to choose include fish sticks and popcorn shrimp. Not only are these fun snacks for your children, but they also make great appetizers. If you like to cook at home, you can find many different kinds of frozen seafood to serve as the basis for your meals, including shrimp, scallops, crawfish tails and even lobster. We also offer a number of different fish fillet options that, when thawed, are as fresh as they were the day they were caught. With these fillets, you can make great fish dishes like broiled salmon, stuffed flounder or breaded catfish.

Frozen vegetables

Even if you're cooking with fresh meat or seafood, it makes food prepping easier to use frozen vegetables to round out your meal. Frozen vegetables are flash frozen the day they were picked, so they taste just like you pulled them from your garden. You can buy virtually every vegetable in frozen form, some with their own premade sauces. Some vegetables come in bags that you can place in a microwave oven to steam within minutes.

One other classic vegetable that you can find in the freezer section? Frozen potatoes. The majority of these fall in the French fry category, but there are other types of frozen potatoes, too, whether you're in the mood for hash browns, tater tots, sweet potatoes, roasted potatoes or mashed potatoes.

Ice cream and novelties

No mention of frozen food would be complete without ice cream. You can buy ice cream in small single-serve cups, pints, quarts, half gallons (or almost half gallons), gallons and 3- to 5-gallon tubs. All your favorite flavors are available, and you can enjoy them plain or with tasty toppings like nuts, fudge, fruits, candy or cookies mixed right into the ice cream. There are also plenty of ice cream novelties available, including chocolate-covered ice cream bars, cones topped with chocolate and nuts, and ice cream sandwiches. If ice cream isn't your ideal treat, fruit-flavored pops and Italian ices are nice treats to have on hand.
